f="https://www.guitarworld.com/" target="_blank" rel="noopener"><em>《吉他世界》</em></a>采访时，主唱<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/smashing-pumpkins-jeff-schroeder-on-whether-he-feels-any-rivalry-with-james-iha-2344280">Billy Corgan 赞扬了 Schroeder</a> ，他说：“看，Jeff 已经为乐队投入了 12 年，这是一个非常认真的承诺。他将自己的一生奉献给了乐队，我觉得这是他应得的。</p><p> “他不仅是一位伟大的音乐家，而且对幕后发生的许多事情也非常负责。我实在看不出如果没有他，这一切还能行得通。”</p><p> Smashing Pumpkins 即将开始两场巡演。他们将与<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/weezer">Weezer</a>一起<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-smashing-pumpkins-and-weezer-announce-2024-uk-and-ireland-tour-buy-tickets-3515603">前往英国和欧洲</a>进行 2024 年夏季联合巡演（门票已<a href="https://www.ticketmaster.co.uk/the-smashing-pumpkins-tickets/artist/736143?irgwc=1&amp;utm_source=2862475-NME%20Networks%20Media%20Limited&amp;utm_medium=affiliate&amp;utm_campaign=2862475&amp;awtrc=&amp;clickId=WyQS5CymqxyNU6mQdCxfu1IQUkFT8TykCzQSQk0&amp;camefrom=CFC_BUYAT_2862475&amp;ircid=7559">在此处</a>发售）。<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/green-day">绿日乐队</a>还宣布<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/green-day-smashing-pumpkins-and-rancid-for-2024-us-stadium-tour-3518681">The Smashing Pumpkins 将支持他们</a>2024 年美国体育场巡演；日期尚未公布。</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/rancid">Rancid</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-linda-lindas">The Linda Lindas</a>也宣布将与 Smashing Pumpkins 一起支持流行朋克三重奏。</p><p> <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-smashing-pumpkins-announce-departure-of-guitarist-jeff-schroeder-3520585">The Smashing Pumpkins 宣布吉他手 Jeff Schroeder 离开的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
 Foals 的 Yannis Philippakis 谈论他为新剧《忏悔录》创作的“残酷”音乐https://www.nme.com/news/music/foals-yannis-philippakis-interview-music-the-confessions-3520532?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=foals-yannis-philippakis-interview-music-the-confessionsAndrew Trendell Tue, 24 Oct 2023 16:28:17 +0000 Music InterviewsMusic NewsNewsIndie https://www.nme.com/?p=3520532 <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="小马驹的雅尼斯·菲利帕基斯 (Yannis Philippakis)。图片来源：Tom Oxley for NME" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p>这位主唱向我们讲述了国家剧院令人震惊的亚历山大·泽尔丁新剧的配乐和“鼓舞人心”的故事，以及他与已故托尼·艾伦期待已久的项目如何终于接近完成</p><p><a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/foals-yannis-philippakis-interview-music-the-confessions-3520532">Foals 的 Yannis Philippakis 谈论他为新剧“The Confessions”创作的“残酷”音乐的帖子</a>首先出现在<a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ; <p><img width="2000" height="1270" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000.jpg" class="attachment-full size-full wp-post-image" alt="小马驹的雅尼斯·菲利帕基斯 (Yannis Philippakis)。图片来源：Tom Oxley for NME" decoding="async" loading="lazy" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/NME-FOALS-Credit-TOM-OXLEY-10_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /></p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/foals">Foals</a>主唱<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/yannis-philippakis">雅尼斯·菲利普基斯 (Yannis Philippakis)</a>接受<em>NME</em>采访，谈论了他的戏剧首秀，为新剧<em>《忏悔录》</em>创作音乐，以及他与已故<a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/TONY-ALLEN">托尼·艾伦 (Tony Allen)</a>酝酿已久的项目。</p><p> <em>《忏悔录》</em>上周在伦敦国家剧院首演，并于昨晚（10 月 23 日）向媒体放映，是一部感人至深、扣人心弦、震撼人心的戏剧，由亚历山大·泽尔丁编剧和导演，讲述了他母亲在八个“动荡”十年中的生活故事跨越两大洲和一系列复杂的关系。</p><p>菲利帕基斯和泽尔丁在上学时就认识了，当时他们会偷偷溜到附近的河岸一起抽烟。这位艺术家在接受<em>《NME》</em>采访时解释了这位导演如何“早在他之前就享有盛誉”，因为他“非常聪明，但也有顽皮的倾向”。</p><p> “我们已经在彼此的生活中生活了很长一段时间，但有着不同的轨道和不同的世界，”菲利帕基斯告诉<em>《NME》</em> 。 “多年来，我们俩一直致力于合作，然后轨道越来越近，我们终于能够一起做出一些东西。”</p><p>他们富有创意的合作伙伴关系在疫情期间取得了成果，当时，当他们被允许时，两人会一起在伦敦周围散步。</p><p> “当天气狂风大作时，我们在布莱克希思和格林威治附近遇到了这一伟大的事件，”菲利帕基斯说。 “就在那时，他刚刚开始谈论写一部作品来概括他母亲的生活的想法。这真的很鼓舞人心。”</p><p>他继续说道：“我对这个故事感到震惊，因为我见过他的母亲几次。我对她的印象是她非常宽容。周日晚上，亚历克斯会邀请人们到他家做客，整个房子里都会有人抽烟。亚历克斯会邀请街头音乐家到他家，第二天早上我们要去学校，而所有这些人都在他母亲面前读诗和吸毒！</p><p> “When he told me the story of some of the things that had happened to her and her arc from growing up in Australia to all of these shocking things that happened to her until she moved to England. Alex described this moment when her mother was nearly pushed off a cliff with murderous intent, and I told him that I could write music for that moment. That&#39;s what bonded me to working on the project.” </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="The Confessions |官方预告片|国家大剧院" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/5xqW1E75oGg?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Explaining how he approached penning music away from the context of an arena-filling indie band, Philippakis recalled it as “a really fascinating learning experience”.</p><p> “Alex was super free in not really giving me any direction,” he said. “It was liberating, and amazing stuff came out of it. I just went on my own to the studio and didn&#39;t really use the guitar at all. Everything started off on a Roland Juno synth, and I&#39;m not a very good synth or keyboard player, so I had to really push myself. It was quite frustrating and slowed down the pace of what I was doing, but I found that tension of not being fully adept at the instrument quite inspiring and gratifying.</p><p> “I ended up writing something quite beautiful out of that perseverance. I would send stuff to Alex and he&#39;d always just encourage me and say, &#39;Go further&#39;.”</p><p> Yannis described the material as “harsh and brutalist in a way” with “metallic blasts of sound”.</p><p> “We refer to one of the repeated sounds as &#39;an ancient elephant&#39; because it sounds like a primal blast from a brutal past,” he said. &#39;I wrote a lot of music for Alex, and kept asking, &#39;How much music can the play and the theatre take?&#39; One big thing I discovered was that what&#39;s right for theatre is very different to what&#39;s right for something filmed.</p><p> “That was a big chasm to understand, and I now have a bunch of very cinematic pieces of music that might be for a different project. A lot of the challenge of doing this has been in approaching how and when the music should be used, supportive and discreet.” </p><figure id="attachment_3520545" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3520545" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3520545" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Lilit-Lesser_2000.jpg" alt="The Confessions, starring Lilit Lesser, Jerry Killick, Pamela Rabe, Eryn Jean Norvill, Joe Bannister - Photo by Christophe Raynaud de Lage" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Lilit-Lesser_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Lilit-Lesser_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Lilit-Lesser_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Lilit-Lesser_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Lilit-Lesser_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Lilit-Lesser_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3520545" class="wp-caption-text"> The Confessions, starring Lilit Lesser, Jerry Killick, Pamela Rabe, Eryn Jean Norvill, Joe Bannister – Photo by Christophe Raynaud de Lage</figcaption></figure><p> The frontman continued: “There&#39;s one piece of music called &#39;A Farewell&#39;, which is my favourite and is super emotive and melancholic. It&#39;s quite manipulative in a way. It&#39;s played quite quietly over a scene where two characters declare a love for one another that&#39;s so passionate it&#39;s almost cannibalistic. It&#39;s beautiful to have actors live inside that musical moment. The first time I saw that was in rehearsals in France, and it was a rush that I&#39;ve never had in the band.</p><p> “Some of the music is super loud and almost attacks the play. There are scenes where it&#39;s confronting, and I really enjoyed making something jarring that fights aspects of the play and shakes the theatre.”</p><p> For Foals fans looking to see the play, the frontman said that they would find “some musical DNA in there that they&#39;ll be familiar with”, and that the score may evolve into something else later down the line.</p><p> “Some of the pieces being used may go on to find their final form in a song,” he said. “There are definitely a couple of pieces that I will finish as songs at some point; I don&#39;t know in what project. By seeing the play, you&#39;re going to see the embryo of something to come.”</p><p> “There are loud and cool sounds, but no spicy indie bangers!”</p><p> From here, Yannis said that he was “open” to doing more soundtrack and score work – particularly with Zeldin – with a dream of eventually penning music for “some kind of crazy, out there, twisted musical”. He also said that he&#39;d be taking away some lessons on staging that may influence future Foals tours, but that the band would be taking time to re-charge after their upcoming shows in Australia to complete touring for 2022&#39;s &#39; <a href="https://www.nme.com/reviews/album/foals-life-is-yours-album-review-3247671">Life Is Yours</a> &#39;. </p><figure id="attachment_3520546" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3520546" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img decoding="async" loading="lazy" class="size-full wp-image-3520546" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Amelda-Brown_2000.jpg" alt="The Confessions, starring Amelda Brown. Photo by Christophe Raynaud de Lage" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Amelda-Brown_2000.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Amelda-Brown_2000-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Amelda-Brown_2000-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Amelda-Brown_2000-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Amelda-Brown_2000-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/Confessions_Amelda-Brown_2000-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="(max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3520546" class="wp-caption-text"> The Confessions, starring Amelda Brown. Photo by Christophe Raynaud de Lage</figcaption></figure><p> After that, Philippakis said that his long-awaited project with the late, great Fela Kuti icon Tony Allen would finally see the light of day – <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/yannis-philippakis-reveals-new-tony-allen-project-discusses-new-foals-album-1964061">having been in the works since 2017</a> , long before <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/pioneering-afrobeat-drummer-tony-allen-dead-79-2657461">the percussionist&#39;s death in 2020</a> .</p><p> “It&#39;s pretty done now,” Yannis revealed. “We&#39;re in the very final mixes. David Wrench [ <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/david-byrne">David Byrne</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/the-xx">The xx</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/frank-ocean">Frank Ocean</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/sampha">Sampha</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/caribou">Caribou</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/blur">Blur</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/arlo-parks">Arlo Parks</a> , <a href="https://www.nme.com/artists/florence-and-the-machine">Florence + The Machine</a> ] has mixed it. It&#39;s going to come out next year.</p><p> “I need to figure out how to present it to the world and come up with a name for it. Hopefully we&#39;ll play some shows to honour the project and to honour Tony. I&#39;m really excited and think people are going to love it.”</p><ul><li> <a href="https://www.nme.com/features/tony-allen-obituary-tribute-2657971"><strong>READ MORE:</strong> Tony Allen, 1940 – 2020: Afrobeat pioneer whose skill and talent inspired the world to skip and swing</a></li></ul><p> Speaking to <em>NME</em> about the project earlier this year, Philippakis said: “The songs have amazing grooves obviously, with Tony Allen on drums. They&#39;re quite dirty, quite rough, fun, polyrhythmic and some of them are quite up-lifting. There&#39;s something generally liberating about having a separate project. It feels like a holiday, in a way. Even thought I always put 100 per cent of myself into everything, by virtue of it not being a Foals project it feels liberating in certain ways.</p><p> “The lyrics are slightly different and slightly more political. They&#39;re less introspective and have more of a social edge. I was walking to studio in Paris through trash-filled streets due to the strikes, so some of that crept in. I don&#39;t want to give too much away. I want it to be a document of the time that we were together in Paris and for it to be faithful to this Parisian band with Tony as the drummer.”</p><p> <em>The Confessions</em> runs at The National Theatre until 4 November. <a href="https://www.nationaltheatre.org.uk/productions/the-confessions/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Visit here</a> for tickets and more information.</p><p> The post <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/foals-yannis-philippakis-interview-music-the-confessions-3520532">Foals&#39; Yannis Philippakis on the “brutal” music he&#39;s written for new play &#39;The Confessions&#39;</a> appeared first on <a rel="nofollow" href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a> .</p> ;
